claim.claim-text:
1. An x-ray radiation therapy and scanning system comprising:
a therapy source adapted to deliver a predetermined dose of treatment x-ray radiation along a therapy axis to a patient positioned in a scan field;
a stationary scanning source producing an electron beam;
a detector positioned to partially circumscribe the scan field, the detector located on a first side of the therapy axis and offset from the therapy axis by a first non-zero angle; and
a target arranged concentric with the detector and located opposite the detector across the scan field, the target located on an opposite second side of the therapy axis and positioned at a different second non-zero angle to the therapy axis such that when the electron beam impinges on the target the target transmits x-ray radiation through the scan field to the detector.

16. An x-ray radiation therapy and scanning system comprising:
a therapy source adapted to deliver a predetermined dose of treatment x-ray radiation along an axis to a patient positioned in a scan field;
a stationary scanning source producing an electron beam;
a pair of detector rings positioned to partially circumscribe the scan field; and
a pair of targets arranged concentric with the detector and located opposite the detector across the scan field, the pair of targets at least partially overlapping the pair of detector rings, the pair of targets being positioned such that when the electron beam impinges on at least one of the targets, the target transmits x-rav radiation through the scan field to at least one detector in the pair of detector rings.
